1962 RED BORDEAUX

The 1962 vintage has never enjoyed the drum beating and frenzied publicity of the ‘59s, ’61s or ’64s. But, like a Cinderella tale, they have something important to offer the wine drinker of today. Because of their relatively early maturing, they are absolutely delightful for present drinking with at least five good years ahead. Their cost has gone up substantially in Bordeaux during the recent months as the '59s and ’61s become scarcer and more expensive.
